A Hong Kong-registered oil tanker leaked 10,810 tons , or 66,000 barrels , of crude oil off South Korea 's stormy west coast on Friday , officials said , in what was estimated to be the nation 's largest maritime oil spill .The spill was believed to be South Korea 's largest , according to the Coast Guard and the ministry .The previously largest oil spill in South Korea happened in 1995 when about 5,035 tons of crude and fuel oil was leaked , according to South Korea 's Yonhap news agency .